{% set rectCode %}<area shape="rect" coords="40,40,320,220"
  href="/rooms/conference" alt="Conference Hall" />

<!-- coords: left, top, right, bottom (pixels) -->{% endset %}

{% set circleCode %}<area shape="circle" coords="500,160,80"
  href="/rooms/server" alt="Server Room" />

<!-- coords: center-x, center-y, radius (pixels) -->{% endset %}

{% set polyCode %}<area shape="poly"
  coords="480,280,760,280,760,460,560,460,480,380"
  href="/rooms/office" alt="Open Office" />

<!-- coords: x1,y1, x2,y2, x3,y3, ... (pixels) -->{% endset %}

{% set defaultCode %}<area shape="default"
  href="/rooms/overview" alt="View building overview" />

<!-- Covers the entire image not matched by other areas -->{% endset %}

{% set fullExampleCode %}<img src="floor-plan.jpg" alt="Office floor plan"
  usemap="#office" width="800" height="500" />

<map name="office">
  <area shape="rect" coords="40,40,320,220"
    href="/rooms/conference" alt="Conference Hall"
    title="Conference Hall — seats 120" />

  <area shape="circle" coords="500,160,80"
    href="/rooms/server" alt="Server Room"
    target="_blank" />

  <area shape="poly"
    coords="480,280,760,280,760,460,560,460,480,380"
    href="/rooms/office" alt="Open Office" />

  <area shape="default"
    href="/rooms" alt="View all rooms" />
</map>{% endset %}

{% set mapAreaCode %}<!-- Modern replacement: percentage coordinates + rich tooltips -->
<image-map>
  <img src="floor-plan.jpg" alt="Office floor plan" />

  <map-area shape="rect" coords="5 8 40 44"
    label="Conference Hall" href="/rooms/conference">
    <strong>Conference Hall</strong>
    <p>Seats 120 people.</p>
  </map-area>

  <map-area shape="circle" coords="62.5 32 10"
    label="Server Room" href="/rooms/server">
    <strong>Server Room</strong>
    <p>24 racks, climate controlled.</p>
  </map-area>
</image-map>{% endset %}

<section>
  <h2>Description</h2>
  <p>The <code>&lt;area&gt;</code> element defines a single clickable region inside an image map. It is always a child of a <a href="/docs/elements/native/map/"><code>&lt;map&gt;</code></a> element. Each area specifies a <code>shape</code>, pixel-based <code>coords</code>, and a destination <code>href</code>.</p>

  <p>The <code>&lt;area&gt;</code> element is a <strong>void element</strong> &mdash; it has no closing tag and cannot contain child content. Tooltip text is limited to the <code>title</code> attribute (plain text only).</p>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Live Demo</h2>

  <p>Hover over a room to see its <code>title</code> tooltip. Click to see the area name. The image renders at its native 800&times;500 pixels so the pixel-based coordinates align correctly.</p>

